A wide, cinematic landscape scene of a Chinese man and woman dressed in elegant ancient Chinese traditional attire, seated across from each other playing a game of Connect Four on a low wooden table. They are positioned in the center of a serene stone courtyard beneath an ornate Chinese gazebo (pavilion). The scene is set in daytime, with soft natural sunlight illuminating the courtyard and casting gentle shadows.  The man wears flowing Hanfu robes in muted jade, charcoal, and ink tones; the woman wears layered silk robes in soft crimson and ivory, her hair styled with traditional ornaments. The modern Connect Four game is subtly integrated, designed with understated wooden tones so it harmonizes naturally with the ancient setting rather than feeling intrusive.
The wide background reveals curved tiled roofs, wooden pillars, bamboo groves, bonsai trees, and hanging silk curtains moving lightly in the breeze. Distant garden walls and mountains fade softly into mist, enhancing depth and tranquility.
Art style: a refined hybrid of traditional Chinese watercolor (ink wash textures, soft gradients, rice-paper feel) and classical oil painting (rich brushstrokes, depth, painterly lighting). Calm, contemplative mood, balanced horizontal composition, museum-quality artwork.
